author: Y Combinator
description: There’s room to rebuild the AI infrastructure stack: better software at inference-layer tooling, cheaper ways to handle GPU workloads, and optimizations that let AI apps scale without bleeding money.
title: Inference AI Infra in the World of Test-Time Compute

author: Y Combinator
description: Just as RedHat and YC W15 company Gitlab built public companies around open source projects, we are looking for companies built around open source AI models like DeepSeek and Llama.
title: AI Commercial Open Source Software (AICOSS)

author: Y Combinator
description:
According to OpenAI's former Chief Research Officer Bob McGrew, AGI is basically already here. So what happens next? In this episode of “How To Build The Future,” YC President and CEO Garry Tan sits down with McGrew to discuss the lessons learned from his time at OpenAI, the promise of personal AI assistants, his advice for startups, and what all of this means for the jobs of the future. 

Apply to Y Combinator: https://ycombinator.com/apply
title: How To Build The AGI Future: Bob McGrew

author: Y Combinator
description: The world’s richest people employ large staffs of humans, like tax accountants, lawyers, money managers, personal trainers, and even private doctors. AI will soon be good enough to do all these jobs for everyone. Who’s building this?
title: AI Personal Staff for Everyone
